begin_memory_text: We talked about video games which was a common interest of us both
middle_memory_text: We talked about life situations and where we were living in the country and what was going on. We also talked about interests a bit which was nice.
end_memory_text: At my partners request we began to talk about politics. We had very different ideas. At the very end she wanted to see my dog which helped to end on a positive note
rest_of_day_open: I see it being a bit hectic. WorkIs becoming very hard and my wife and I have a busy weekend which a lot of activities. It would be nice to have some downtime but I don’t see that happening anytime soon. I am hoping to get some rest though which would be nice.
critical_positive: My partner was tired so I tried to carry it a bit and make it reciprocal. She was very friendly and easy to talk to which was nice. She also seemed very good natured. We definitely had some common interests which is nice and it made the conversation flow more easily.
critical_negative: We had very different political views. I could tell she was getting upset with my opinion. I knew she would. She didn’t understand my point of view which was completely fine but I could tell it made things a bit awkward for her which made the conversation die down a bit

begin_memory_text: I believe we talked about videogames and where we were from - he talked about playing Kingdom Hearts with his 4 year old daughter. He talked about the PC he built, and the Raspberry Pi gaming thing he had...I talked about the fires a little bit. I mentioned being sleep deprived/bad conversationalist
middle_memory_text: I talked about the fires in Colorado (maybe that was the beginning though?) we talked about hobbies...I'm remembering we talked more about his job in the beginning so in the middle we talked about videogames, he talked about his Facebook friend making terrible t-shirts haha. We talked about my hobbies and stuff
end_memory_text: We were talking about politics, voting for trump, immigration...I started getting the sense he was really racist in a subtle way and it made me uncomfortable. We talked about taxes, the economy, Trump being a despicable person. At the very very end he showed me his dog (and mentioned his dog was previously abused...and told me a story of the "one time" he hit his dog, which also made me uncomfortable..)it got weird all around at the end but we were cordial.
rest_of_day_open: I have a stressful rest of the week, have to rescue a bunch of items from my boyfriend's family house in an evacuation zone near the Colorado wildfires. Have an appointment to go to and have a ton of errands to run...I feel overwhelmed already. But I will cope with it the best I can.
critical_positive: He was generally kind and the conversation flowed pretty well, there weren't any super awkward/painful moments (well, for the most part). Even when we were talking about difficult things we managed to stay pretty nice and understanding towards each other. He seemed like a good-hearted family-oriented person (for the most part). I enjoyed talking about videogames/hobbies with him.
critical_negative: It was basically my fault for introducing politics haha but when he said he would vote for Trump...and I realized a lot of the racist shit he had been subtly-saying was far more overtly racist than I wanted to believe (I like to give people the benefit of the doubt...) and it made me deeply uncomfortable. I generally began to feel like "maybe this guy isn't as nice as he seems," because he kept justifying his vote for Trump with bordering-on-racist tangents and we were so far on opposite sides of the political spectrum I didn't know how to respond...yet he agreed with me that Trump was despicable? It was generally kind of saddening/frustrating to listen to.
